==Finnish==
{{Finnish index|s|a}}

===Etymology===
From {{inh|fi|fiu-fin-pro|*saattadak}}. Equivalent to {{suffix|fi|saada|alt1=saa|ttaa}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{hyphenation|fi|saat|taa}}
* {{rhymes|fi|ɑːtːɑː}}
* {{fi-IPA|*}}

===Verb===
{{fi-verb}} {{lb|fi|transitive}}

# to [[escort]], [[usher]], [[see]], [[accompany]], [[walk]]
#: '''''Saatatko''' minut kotiin?''
#:: Will you '''walk''' me home?
# ''~ [[ulos]]'': to [[see off]] {{gloss|to accompany someone to a point of departure}}
# to [[bring]], [[drive]] (''into a situation'')
#: ''Olet '''saattanut''' minut häpeään.''
#:: You have '''brought''' me to shame.
# {{lb|fi|auxiliary|+ infinitive}} [[may]] (do, probably do); (''in the conditional mood'') [[might]] (do, probably do)
# {{lb|fi|auxiliary|+ infinitive; in simple past tense}} to [[have]] the [[impudence]]/[[nerve]] (to do), [[dare]] ((to) do), [[be able to]] (do).
#: ''[[miten|Miten]] [[sinä]] '''saatoit''' [[arvostella]] [[me#Finnish|meitä]]?''
#:: ''How '''dare''' you criticize us?''

